The United States is concerned about recent developments in Burma, including the arrest of State Counselor Aung San Suu Kyi and other civilian officials. President Biden has been briefed on the situation and the US affirms its support for Burma's democratic institutions. The US urges the military and all parties involved to adhere to democratic norms and the rule of law, and to release those who have been detained. The US opposes any attempt to alter the outcome of recent elections or hinder Myanmar's democratic transition, and will take action against those responsible if necessary. The US is closely monitoring the situation and stands with the people of Burma in their pursuit of democracy and peace.